      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DYNAMITEDAN (11) was a fair way from the winner when fourth in his heat but that was his first outing for six months so he should be better for it. May need some luck from this draw but he has ability having won two of his first four starts, both at Menangle including the rich APG Sydney Sales Graduate Series final. SOHO WASHINGTON (1) came from a much wider barrier for a sound third at Menangle two back before filling the same placing in last week's heat at this circuit and distance. Looks close to a win and should get his chance from the ace draw. REWATCH (2) draws lower than when fourth last week and did kick off his campaign with a Menangle in last month. Owns a good record at this distance and should be peaking now. EMPEROR (5) has come from wider barriers in his five starts to date, winning twice. Has some upside and could be competitive from this draw.",
